  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Regional Gender and HIV Capacity Strengthening Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Considering the difficult HIV funding environment and the team capacity/workload and after reviewing the Central American partners involved in gender and HIV work it was determined during strategic planning work in Managua team that the HIV programme has completed a first phase and that it is not necessary to maintain it as an exclusive programme on its own.  It is proposed that HIV as a cross-cutting theme and gender, another CAFOD priority area, be linked offering greater manoeuvring possibilities. Consequently, this proposal is for Gender and HIV to be a capacity strengthening programme for all those CAFOD-CA partners who want to partake in it. In 2017-18, this project will support CAM regional networking activities, such as the one organized by former CAFOD partner Cantera, with participation of Guatemalan partner, Pastoral Social Caritas Diocese of Verapaz. 
In 2019, Cantera is working on a virtual network platform on gender methodologies, which will include CAFOD partners in Central America and other organisations working on gender.
In 2020, an evaluation - lessons learned process for the Regional Gender and HIV Capacity Strengthening Programme  is going to take place</narrative>
  </description>
